hat Do PUMA’s Customers Want?

PUMA's customer base is driven by a multifaceted desire for products that blend high performance with contemporary style. Consumers seek apparel and footwear that not only enhance their athletic capabilities but also reflect current fashion trends, offering comfort, durability, and an ergonomic fit for both sport and leisure.

Performance and Style Integration

Customers look for sportswear that boosts athletic performance and aligns with fashion. They value comfort, durability, and ergonomic designs for ease of movement.

Technological Innovation

The brand addresses practical needs through R&D, incorporating technologies like NITROTM foam in running and basketball gear. Innovative features are also present in their football product lines.

Brand Values and Sustainability

Environmentally conscious consumers are drawn to PUMA's commitment to sustainability and ethical practices. Over half of 18-27 year olds globally seek greater brand transparency on environmental impact.

Sustainability Goals

PUMA aims for 90% of its products to use recycled or certified materials by 2025. Initiatives like RE:FIBRE focus on textile recycling, demonstrating a commitment to environmental stewardship.

Influencer Marketing and Collaborations

Collaborations with athletes like Neymar Jr. and cultural figures such as Rihanna generate significant brand visibility. These partnerships appeal to trendsetters and enhance brand appeal.

Digital Engagement

The brand actively engages its audience through social media platforms like Instagram, TikTok, and YouTube. These channels are used for product launches, influencer collaborations, and brand storytelling.

Addressing Consumer Pain Points

Customer purchasing behavior is influenced by product exclusivity and availability, with some consumers noting high prices and limited access to special releases as pain points. Understanding these aspects is key to the Mission, Vision & Core Values of PUMA.

